          </setup>
          <statement>
            <p permid="oKX">
              A line <m>\kappa</m> is parallel to the line with equation <m>y=-3.5x+17</m>,
              but <m>\kappa</m> passes through the point <m>(-12,23)</m>.
              What is an equation for <m>\kappa</m>?
            </p>

            <p permid="USg">
              <var name="$line" width="20" />
            </p>
          </statement>
          <solution permid="FuN">
            <p permid="QDM">
              Parallel lines have the same slope,
              and the slope of <m>y=-3.5x+17</m> is <m>-3.5</m>.
              So <m>\kappa</m> has slope <m>-3.5</m>.
              And we know a point that <m>\kappa</m> passes through,
              so we can use point-slope form to write its equation as
              <me permid="EDP">
                y=-3.5(x+12)+23\text{.}
              </me>
            </p>
